        SUNDAY FOCUS A11 THE SUNDAY TIMES SUNDAY, NOVEMBER 22, 2020 | | | ● • For the team/department • Train representa­tives to spot signs of mental distress, and on where they can refer employees to seek help. • Have open conversati­ons on mental well-being. - Schedule regular check-ins with employees and review their workloads. • Strengthen social support system.
- Form informal support networks such as parenting support groups. Organise bonding activities. • • Implement flexible work arrangemen­ts. - Flexi-place such as telecommut­ing or work-from-home.
- Flexi-time such as staggered working hours or compressed work week.
- Flexi-load such as part-time work or job-sharing. • Establish work-life harmony policy and offer clarity on after-hours work communicat­ion.
- Make clear that for messages sent after work hours, a reply is not expected until the next working day, except for those marked as urgent.
- If employees need to work after-hours, consider giving them time off to have adequate rest. Source: TRIPARTITE ADVISORY ON MENTAL WELL-BEING AT WORKPLACES SUNDAY TIMES GRAPHICS PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
